In the province of Utrecht, the churches had not been distributed into certain Classes, wherefore it pleased the States of that province that all the Remonstrants should meet together apart in one Synod3 but the rest of the pastors, who did not follow the opinion of the Remonstrants, of whom there still re- mained no small number, in another (Synod,) and that from each Synod and party three should be sent forth to the national Synod with the power of judging.
